EDA for single category dataset¶

-- top 100 products with most reviews -- top 100 products with highest avg rating -- top 100 reviewers who gave most reviews and avg ratings they usually gave -- review trend -- word cloud(positive and negative reviews) -- LDA topic analysis(by getting the main topics of reviews, we can get some ideas of what are people mainly talking about in the reviews, and what are they truly care)

not sure but working on it¶

add a category_name column to every single category dataset, and merge them together into one dataframe

using this dataframe to compare the avg ratings of different category, and compare the review trends on positive and negative ratings(convert 1-5 ratings to binary variable)

In [64]:
# create new data frame with reviewTime and overall columns
dff = new_df[['reviewTime','overall']]

# extract only year and month from reviewTime
dff = dff.withColumn("reviewTime",date_format("reviewTime", 'yyyy/MM'))

dff = dff.orderBy(col("reviewTime").asc())#no .show(), if dff = dff.orderBy(col("reviewTime").asc()).show()

#get five different dataframes based on overall ratings[1-5], and count the total number of the ratings on different month
dff_1 = dff.filter(dff.overall ==1).groupby('reviewTime').count().orderBy("reviewTime")
dff_2 = dff.filter(dff.overall ==2).groupby('reviewTime').count().orderBy("reviewTime")
dff_3 = dff.filter(dff.overall ==3).groupby('reviewTime').count().orderBy("reviewTime")
dff_4 = dff.filter(dff.overall ==4).groupby('reviewTime').count().orderBy("reviewTime")
dff_5 = dff.filter(dff.overall ==5).groupby('reviewTime').count().orderBy("reviewTime")

#transform into pandas dataframe to make plot
dff_1 = dff_1.toPandas()
dff_2 = dff_2.toPandas()
dff_3 = dff_3.toPandas()
dff_4 = dff_4.toPandas()
dff_5 = dff_5.toPandas()

plt.plot_date(x=dff_3['reviewTime'],y=dff_3['count'],label='Overall_rating=3')
plt.plot_date(x=dff_4['reviewTime'],y=dff_4['count'],label='Overall_rating=4')

plt.ylabel('Number of review',fontsize=22)
